\par\plain {\f2\fs26\b0\i1 Before Transition:}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\fi360\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 After all the paperwork had been signed by Evan, Sarah, and Liz, Sarah's senior attorney, and Evan\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s attorney shook hands in a show of equal respect. Sarah's senior attorney said a few words to her, shook her hand, and left the conference room. Evan's attorney asked Evan to step out of the room because he wanted to offer Evan some advice before he returned to the conference room to meet with Sarah alone. With the attorneys and Evan out of the conference room, Sarah and Liz were left alone.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>Sarah<!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::1>(feeling shame):<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf6 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You don't hate me, do you?"<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>Liz:<!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf6 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Why would I hate you, Sarah?"<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>Sarah:<!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf6 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Because of how close you and Evan are, and seeing him so hurt..."<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::1>[Sarah sighed deeply.]<!$Scr_Cs::1>}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>Sarah:<!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf6 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I never wanted to hurt him. You understand why I had to do this, right?"<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>Liz<!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::1>(Understanding and Compassionate)<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 :}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf6 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes, I understand, and no, I don't hate you."<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>Sarah<!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f3\fs26\b0\i1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::1> (self-pitying):<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf6 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I bet everyone at Vaughn Group is bad-mouthing me. They probably think I'm the worst."<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch \f0\fs26\b0\i0
\par\plain \f0\fs26\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs26\b0\i1 End Transition:}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\fi360\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs26\b0\i0 After the formalities of signing the divorce papers were concluded, Sarah watched as the attorneys exchanged courteous nods, marking an end to the official proceedings. Evan\loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8217\'92s attorney whispered a few parting words of advice to Evan, guiding him out for a private conversation, leaving the conference room steeped in a heavy silence. Now alone, Sarah and Liz faced each other, an ocean of unspoken emotions swirling between them.}
\par\plain {\f4\fs26\b0\i0 Sarah\loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8217\'92s voice was low, tinged with vulnerability. \u8220\'93You don\u8217\'92t hate me, do you?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f4\fs26\b0\i0 Liz met her gaze, her expression softening. \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Why would I hate you, Sarah?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f4\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s just... seeing how close you and Evan are, and him being so hurt...\u8221\'94 Sarah\u8217\'92s voice trailed off as she exhaled a heavy sigh, the weight of her actions pressing down on her.}
\par\plain {\f4\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93I never wanted to hurt him. You understand why I had to do this, right?\u8221\'94 Sarah\u8217\'92s eyes searched Liz\u8217\'92s for some sign of understanding.}
\par\plain {\f4\fs26\b0\i0 Liz nodded, her voice warm and reassuring. \loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8220\'93Yes, I understand, and no, I don\u8217\'92t hate you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f4\fs26\b0\i0 Sarah\loch\af4\hich\af4\dbch\af4\uc1\u8217\'92s shoulders slumped slightly, relief momentarily lightening the burden she carried. \u8220\'93I bet everyone in the office is bad-mouthing me. They probably think I\u8217\'92m the worst.\u8221\'94}
